    <body>
      <trans-unit id="1" ns:sid="2047271442947567624" ns:tid="2047271755365429250" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="65">
        <source>Why Is PV Power Not Used to Charge the Battery?</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="2" ns:sid="2047271442947567625" ns:tid="2047271755365429251" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="39">
        <source>Economic returns first</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="3" ns:sid="2047271442947567626" ns:tid="2047271755365429252" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="42">
        <source>When PV power is generated, if the feed-in electricity price (peak feed-in electricity price) is higher than or close to the net returns from charging and then discharging the battery, the system will prioritize selling the PV power directly to the grid.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="4" ns:sid="2047271442947567627" ns:tid="2047271755365429253" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="56">
        <source><ph id="f0">&lt;uicontrol class=&quot;+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol &quot; id=&quot;uicontrol1891019245456&quot; conref=&quot;en-us_topic_0000207784470567.xml#438333&quot; idp:conrefpath=&quot;200650494000#EN-US_BOOKMAP_0000002298266790#EN-US_TOPIC_0000207784470567&quot;/&gt;</ph> charging window and <ph id="f1">&lt;uicontrol class=&quot;+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol &quot; id=&quot;uicontrol55241626133415&quot; conref=&quot;en-us_topic_0000207635068172.xml#456541&quot; idp:conrefpath=&quot;200650494000#EN-US_BOOKMAP_0000002298267098#EN-US_TOPIC_0000207635068172&quot;/&gt;</ph> mode restrictions</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="5" ns:sid="2047271442947567628" ns:tid="2047271755365429254" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="31">
        <source>If the charging window does not cover the PV generation period (for example, the PV peak is at noon but the charging window is set in the early morning), the PV power is used first to meet home load demand, with the remainder sold directly to the grid rather than stored.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="6" ns:sid="2047271442947567629" ns:tid="2047271755365429255" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="65">
        <source>System status and forecast</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="7" ns:sid="2047271442947567630" ns:tid="2047271755365429256" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="65">
        <source><bpt id="g0">&lt;b class=&quot;+ topic/ph hi-d/b &quot; id=&quot;b1977617109417&quot;&gt;</bpt>High SOC<ept id="g0">&lt;/g&gt;</ept>:</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8" ns:sid="2047271442947567631" ns:tid="2047271755365429257" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="52">
        <source>If the SOC has reached the preset end-of-charge threshold (for example, 90%), the system stops charging to prevent overcharging.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="9" ns:sid="2047271442947567632" ns:tid="2047271755365429258" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="54">
        <source>In this case, the PV power is fed to the grid or supplied to loads.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10" ns:sid="2047271442947567633" ns:tid="2047271755365429259" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="Intelligente [planning]" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="79">
        <source><bpt id="g0">&lt;b class=&quot;+ topic/ph hi-d/b &quot; id=&quot;b4442195415911&quot;&gt;</bpt>Intelligent scheduling policy<ept id="g0">&lt;/g&gt;</ept>:</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match">Intelligente [planning]</target>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="11" ns:sid="2047271442947567634" ns:tid="2047271755365429260" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="48">
        <source>The <ph id="f0">&lt;ph class=&quot;- topic/ph &quot; conref=&quot;en-us_topic_0000001645659009.xml#ph122067484595&quot; id=&quot;ph1959151418587&quot; idp:conrefpath=&quot;200650494000#EN-US_BOOKMAP_0000001596019118#EN-US_TOPIC_0000001645659009&quot; idp:userph=&quot;true&quot;/&gt;</ph> forecasts the future electricity prices and load.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="12" ns:sid="2047271442947567635" ns:tid="2047271755365429261" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="25">
        <source>If the system forecasts that electricity prices will be lower or PV output will be more abundant later, it may delay charging and wait for a better opportunity.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
    </body>
